rComments: He has a very dark sense of humour which keeps you awake and attentive in class. He pretends to give off the vibe that he's a "tough-love" prof but in reality he's a softie which is really nice and hard to find in a prof. His nature makes you want to study and try harder in class. I really hope I can take more classes with him once he comes back.
Interesting, funny, and nice. Straightforward class. Easy to pass, never studied, just attended all lectures and tutorials. Not a challenging class at all, great prof

Not as easy as some expect. The assignments were fun and involved going out and doing research. You really need to study well for the midterm and the exam for the year of 2015 was nothing like the previous exams. However, Leydon is a fun professor, uses goods examples, and provides great clarification if you go see him during his office hours.

Witty and interesting. Liked the class, pretty straightforward. Assignments required you to go out into the world and actually learn first hand about retail geography, which made them interesting. Recommend.
Amazing! Hilarious! Really really cares about his students. Very relate able and always willing to help
He was amazing professor and always engaged his students !! always wanted us to do well thank you!
Really helpful! Engaging lectures. Not boring whatsoever. Work hard and you will be fine. Definitely one of the most accessible profs at UTM; open-door office hour policy. My favourite!

Class was always fun with him. Had him for two classes, and hopefully some more. He is hilarious, there wasnt one lecture where I didn't smile and laugh. Tests are easy, but assignments are brutal. The TAs mark VERY hard. One TA gave me a 57, showed an unmarked version to another TA and gave me 75 (Mark wasn't changed tho).

Such an awesome prof!!  Completely hilarious, so interesting and really wants his students to succeed. I have a low attendance level in most classes but he was so interesting that I always wanted to go to class!
My favorate prof at university! Funny and clear, and very approachable=)

He's funny, tests are easy, but assignments can bebrutal depending your TA is, some TA' mark easy (90s) others will give you 60s. I went to ask him why I lost a few marks, he is NOT approachable, didn't help at all and brought my mark down even more. People who used similar ideas but had diff TA's got high 80s. There are better GGR courses at UTM!

Prof Joseph Leydon is the BEST! Lectures are super clear, interesting, and he knows the material. Tests are easy if you attend practicals. He cares about his students and loves cracking jokes, I laugh at all of them! If only he was a permanent prof at UTM! I was so sad to leave the last day of class ;( Super nice man and love his Irish accent too!
NICEST PROF EVER ! loved his jokes !! he's willing to help us out when our class average was low. would love to be in his class  again !
Awesome prof :D He marks his tests fairly and the assignments are written out step by step so it's more or less idiot-proof. Marks leniently as well.
